summary: This code uses Expect (a scripting language for automating interactions with programs) to spawn a zsh shell, retrieve and print the current directory three times using "pwd" command, and then exit after receiving end-of-file signal.

details.comment: This code uses Expect (a scripting language for automating interactions with programs) to spawn a zsh shell, retrieve and print the current directory three times using "pwd" command, and then exit after receiving end-of-file signal.
details.content:
#!/data/data/com.termux/files/usr/bin/expect
spawn zsh
expect -re ".*"
puts $expect_out(buffer)
send -- "pwd\r"
expect -re ".*"
puts $expect_out(buffer)
send -- "pwd\r"
expect -re ".*"
puts $expect_out(buffer)
send -- "pwd\r"
expect eof
puts $expect_out(buffer)
